            <title>[JCR-1697] Simple Google style query</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1697</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>In the Sling project there&amp;#39;s a need for a simple query language. See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SLING-573&quot; title=&quot;google-style shorthand on query.json&quot;&gt;SLING-573&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;ve created a parser that translates the simple query into an XPath query statement and executes it on a JCR workspace.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
I&amp;#39;ll commit it to the jackrabbit-jcr-commons module.</description>
